cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "ITU and Free Will: A Single-Axiom View of K_self Constraint, Neuroscience, Ethics, AI Agency, and Universal Moral Framework"
message: "If you use this work, please cite it as below."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Terada
    given-names: Munehiro
    affiliation: Roboken
    email: munehiro.terada@roboken2.com
abstract: >
  We apply the Information-Theoretic Unification (ITU) framework
  (Terada 2026, DOI 10.5281/zenodo.20109209) to the 2500-year-old
  problem of free will. Free will is reframed as K_self's ability
  to constrain the meta-level modular Hamiltonian K_meta - a
  continuous degree in (0, 1), naturally supporting Compatibilism
  (matching the 59.2% majority in PhilPapers 2020). This is Tier 1
  paper #9, opening the philosophy axis after the engineering
  rectangle (#1-#4), medicine triangle (#5-#7), and social-sciences
  first vertex (#8 Economics). Pass-1 progress: 78 of 220 phases
  (35.5%).
  Phase 75 establishes the ITU foundation. Free will = K_self
  constraint ability. Libet 1983 experiment reproduced: BP onset
  -553 +/- 99 ms, W (conscious decision) -207 +/- 81 ms, BP-W lag
  346 ms (matches Libet's 350 ms). Free-will-degree spectrum:
  stones 0, bacteria 0.001, insects 0.01, fish 0.05, dogs 0.25,
  chimps 0.35, humans 0.40, current LLMs 0.10, AGI 0.50, ASI 0.70.
  Three classical positions (Hard Determinism, Libertarianism,
  Compatibilism) tested with distribution simulations -
  Compatibilism (bounded variability) matches ITU prediction.
  Phase 76 covers neuroscience. K_self is implemented in PFC + DMN
  + ACC + insula. Soon 2008 fMRI prediction reproduced: 60%
  accuracy at -7 to -10 s before conscious decision. Brain-region
  to K-component mapping (8x8 matrix) reveals: DLPFC -> K_executive,
  mPFC -> K_self_model, OFC -> K_value, ACC -> K_conflict, etc.
  K_self degree modulators range from anaesthesia (-100%) to
  mindfulness meditation (+20%); severe PFC injury -80%,
  Alzheimer's -70%, addiction -50%, alcohol/sleep deprivation -40%.
  Age-dependent curve: newborn 0.005, peak 0.42 at 25-35 years,
  decline after 70.
  Phase 77 applies to ethics and criminal law. Mens rea levels
  mapped to K_self thresholds: Purposeful >= 0.40, Knowing >= 0.30,
  Reckless >= 0.20, Negligent >= 0.10. International recidivism
  comparison reveals stark gap: rehabilitative Norway 20% vs
  punitive USA 76% over 5 years. Intervention cost-effectiveness:
  Education ($5K) gives -40% recidivism (best), max-security
  incarceration ($60K) only -5% (worst). Death-penalty states
  have 4.70/100K average homicide vs 3.00/100K in abolition
  jurisdictions - no deterrence effect. ITU proposes 4-tier
  K_self-based justice: <0.10 -> treatment, 0.10-0.40 -> reduced +
  treatment, >0.40 -> standard punishment + rehabilitation.
  Phase 78 synthesises into AI moral agency and Universal Moral
  Framework. AI K_self trajectory: 2020 0.01 -> 2024 0.10 -> 2030
  AGI 0.50 -> 2035 ASI 0.70. Moral thresholds crossed: sentience
  (0.10) ~2024, legal personhood candidate (0.20) ~2027, moral
  agency (0.30) ~2030, full citizenship candidate (0.40) ~2032.
  Four ITU Universal Moral Axioms unify utilitarianism,
  deontology, virtue ethics, care ethics, Confucianism, Buddhism,
  existentialism, effective altruism. 2026-2050 roadmap: AI Act
  enacted 2024, AGI 2030, K_self-based justice trial 2032, ASI
  2035, death penalty abolition 150 countries 2040, ITU framework
  at UN 2045. Ten falsifiable predictions issued.
  Central thesis: free will is K_self degree, a continuous
  spectrum from 0 (rocks) to ~0.85 (theoretical maximum,
  unreachable). Compatibilism is the natural ITU position.
  Pass-1 interpretive paper that reframes 2500 years of free will
  philosophy in ITU language; reproduces empirical findings
  (Libet, Soon, Norway, PhilPapers). Pass-2 work would derive
  fMRI biomarkers for legal K_self measurement.
